Finite runner created with CSFML.

USAGE
 ./my_runner map.txt


OPTIONS
 -i                launch the game in infinity mode.
 -h                print the usage and quit.

USER INTERACTIONS
 SPACE_KEY        jump.

THING I HAVE PUT IN THE GAME

 MUST :

 -The window must be closed using events.
 -The program must manage the input from the keyboard.
 -The program must contain animated sprites rendered thanks to sprite sheets.
 -The program must contain moving elements.
 -The program background must include a parallax scrolling with at least 3
  objects moving at different speeds.
 -The program must display a score which is update regularly during the game.
 -The program must handle basic game physics.
 -The program must take a file in argument which will contain the map
 of your current game.
 -The program must have at least one music and one sound effect.

 SHOULD :

 -The program should have randomly spawning obstacles.
 -Animations and movements in your program should not depend on the speed
  of your computer.
 -Animations and movements in your program should be timed by sfClock elements.
 -Your window should stick between 800x600 pixels and 1920x1080 pixels.
 -Your window should have a limited frame rate such that it can be compute
  without lagging.
 -The program should accept the “-h” option, then display usage of the program.
 -Possible user interactions should be explicitly explained in a usage.

 COULD :

 -The program could have an infinite mode where you generate randomly the
  map till the player dies.
